Citation.sAuthor: Prasad, T. E. V.[T. E. Vittal]
Citation.sTitle: Excess Gibbs' energies of the binary mixtures formed by N,N-dimethylformamide with xylenes and cresols at 95.1 kPa
Citation.sAbstract: Bubble point temperatures at 95.1 kPa, over the entire composition range are measured for the binary mixtures of N,N-dimethylformamide with: ortho-, meta-, and para-, xylenes and cresols, making use of a Swietoslawski type ebulliometer. The liquid phase mole fraction versus temperature measurements could be represented well by theWilson model. The optimumWilson parameters are used to calculate the: vapor phase composition, activity coefficients and excess Gibbs energy. The results are discussed.
